SUMMARY:Full Moon Hike at Sugarloaf Park
DESCRIPTION:Bring a flashlight and your sense of wonder as you explore the park after dark on Monday\, March 2\, 4:15-7:00 pm. This moderate-to-strenuous\, 4.2-mile hike with approximately 800ft of elevation gain heads up to the viewpoint on Vista Trail where we will see the moon rise over the Mayacamas and the sun set over Sonoma Valley. Not recommended for children under 7 years old. \nMeet at the White Barn parking lot at least 10 minutes prior to 4:15pm for a prompt departure. Tickets are $10 general\, $5 for students\, youth (12-17 year olds)\, Sugarloaf members\, Sugarloaf or RFO volunteers\, and free for children 7-12 years old. All minors must be accompanied by a parent or legal guardian. You must register to attend; tickets will not be available on site. Bring your flashlight\, at least a quart of water\, extra layers for the evening\, and if desired\, a snack. Parking fees apply.
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/full-moon-hike-at-sugarloaf-park/
LOCATION:Sugarloaf Ridge State Park\, 2605 Adobe Canyon Rd\, Kenwood\, CA
CATEGORIES:Recreation
GEO:38.4427;-122.533
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Sugarloaf Ridge State Park 2605 Adobe Canyon Rd Kenwood CA;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=2605 Adobe Canyon Rd:geo:-122.533,38.4427
END:VEVENT
